{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.21",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 21 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:1",
      "text": "My son, hast thou sinned? do so no more: but for thy former sins also pray that they may be forgiven thee.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:2",
      "text": "Flee from sins as from the face of a serpent: for if thou comest near them, they will take hold of thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:3",
      "text": "The teeth thereof are the teeth of a lion, killing the souls of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:4",
      "text": "All iniquity is like a two-edged sword, there is no remedy for the wound thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:5",
      "text": "Injuries and wrongs will waste riches: and the house that is very rich shall be brought to nothing by pride: so the substance of the proud shall be rooted out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:6",
      "text": "The prayer out of the mouth of the poor shall reach the ears of God, and judgment shall come for him speedily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:7",
      "text": "He that hateth to be reproved walketh in the trace of a sinner: and he that feareth God will turn to his own heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:8",
      "text": "He that is mighty by a bold tongue is known afar off, but a wise man knoweth to slip by him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:9",
      "text": "He that buildeth his house at other men's charges, is as he that gathereth himself stones to build in the winter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:10",
      "text": "The congregation of sinners is like tow heaped together, and the end of them is a flame of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:11",
      "text": "The way of sinners is made plain with stones, and in their end is hell, and darkness, and pains.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:12",
      "text": "He that keepeth justice shall get the understanding thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:13",
      "text": "The perfection of the fear of God is wisdom and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:14",
      "text": "He that is not wise in good, will not be taught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:15",
      "text": "But there is a wisdom that aboundeth in evil: and there is no understanding where there is bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:16",
      "text": "The knowledge of a wise man shall abound like a flood, and his counsel continueth like a fountain of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:17",
      "text": "The heart of a fool is like a broken vessel, and no wisdom at all shall it hold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:18",
      "text": "A man of sense will praise every wise word he shall hear, and will apply it to himself: the luxurious man hath heard it, and it shall displease him, and he will cast it behind his back.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:19",
      "text": "The talking of a fool is like a burden in the way: but in the lips of the wise, grace shall be found.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:20",
      "text": "The mouth of the prudent is sought after in the church, and they will think upon his words in their hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:21",
      "text": "As a house that is destroyed, so is wisdom to a fool: and the knowledge of the unwise is as words without sense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:22",
      "text": "Doctrine to a fool is as fetters on the feet, and like manacles on the right hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:23",
      "text": "A fool lifteth up his voice in laughter: but a wise man will scarce laugh low to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:24",
      "text": "Learning to the prudent is as an ornament of gold, and like a bracelet upon his right arm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:25",
      "text": "The foot of a fool is soon in his neighbour's house: but a man of experience will be abashed at the person of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:26",
      "text": "A fool will peep through the window into the house: but he that is well taught will stand without.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:27",
      "text": "It is the folly of a man to hearken at the door: and a wise man will be grieved with the disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:28",
      "text": "The lips of the unwise will be telling foolish things: but the words of the wise shall be weighed in a balance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:29",
      "text": "The heart of fools is in their mouth: and the mouth of wise men is in their heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:30",
      "text": "While the ungodly curseth the devil, he curseth his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.21.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:31",
      "text": "The talebearer shall defile his own soul, and shall be hated by all: and he that shall abide with him shall be hateful: the silent and wise man shall be honoured.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
